    "body": "This seems to be because in beacon-chain/sync/subscriber.go lines 75+\r\n```\r\n\tif featureconfig.Get().DisableDynamicCommitteeSubnets {\r\n\t\tfor i := uint64(0); i < params.BeaconNetworkConfig().AttestationSubnetCount; i++ {\r\n\t\t\ts.subscribe(\r\n\t\t\t\tfmt.Sprintf(\"/eth2/%%x/beacon_attestation_%d\", i),\r\n\t\t\t\ts.validateCommitteeIndexBeaconAttestation,   /* validator */\r\n\t\t\t\ts.committeeIndexBeaconAttestationSubscriber, /* message handler */\r\n\t\t\t)\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n```\r\nIn the call to subscribe, when i=0, something like \"/eth2/%x/beacon_attestation_0\" is passed as the topic string:\r\n```\r\nfunc (s *Service) subscribe(topic string, validator pubsub.ValidatorEx, handle subHandler) *pubsub.Subscription {\r\n\tbase := p2p.GossipTopicMappings[topic]\r\n\tif base == nil {\r\n\t\tpanic(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s is not mapped to any message in GossipTopicMappings\", topic))\r\n\t}\r\n\treturn s.subscribeWithBase(base, s.addDigestToTopic(topic), validator, handle)\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\np2p.GossipTopicMappings[\"/eth2/%x/beacon_attestation_0\"] is nil and causes the panic.\r\n\r\nWithin gossip_topic_mappings.go\r\n\r\n```\r\nvar GossipTopicMappings = map[string]proto.Message{\r\n\t\"/eth2/%x/beacon_block\":               &pb.SignedBeaconBlock{},\r\n\t\"/eth2/%x/beacon_attestation_%d\":      &pb.Attestation{},\r\n\t\"/eth2/%x/voluntary_exit\":             &pb.SignedVoluntaryExit{},\r\n\t\"/eth2/%x/proposer_slashing\":          &pb.ProposerSlashing{},\r\n\t\"/eth2/%x/attester_slashing\":          &pb.AttesterSlashing{},\r\n\t\"/eth2/%x/beacon_aggregate_and_proof\": &pb.SignedAggregateAttestationAndProof{},\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n\"/eth2/%x/beacon_attestation_%d\" is set to &pb.Attestation{} but \"/eth2/%x/beacon_attestation_0\" (or _1, _2, _3...) are not set to anything.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately I do not know enough about pub/sub and the consequences or semantics of DisableDynamicCommitteeSubnets for ETH2 to really solve this.  Changing beacon-chain/sync/subscriber.go lines 75+ to be something like \r\n\r\n```\r\n\tif featureconfig.Get().DisableDynamicCommitteeSubnets {\r\n\t\tfor i := uint64(0); i < params.BeaconNetworkConfig().AttestationSubnetCount; i++ {\r\n\t\t\tp2p.GossipTopicMappings[fmt.Sprintf(\"/eth2/%%x/beacon_attestation_%d\",i)] = &pb.Attestation{}\r\n\t\t\ts.subscribe(\r\n\t\t\t\tfmt.Sprintf(\"/eth2/%%x/beacon_attestation_%d\", i),\r\n\t\t\t\ts.validateCommitteeIndexBeaconAttestation,   /* validator */\r\n\t\t\t\ts.committeeIndexBeaconAttestationSubscriber, /* message handler */\r\n\t\t\t)\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n```\r\n(All that is added is p2p.GossipTopicMappings[fmt.Sprintf(\"/eth2/%%x/beacon_attestation_%d\",i)] = &pb.Attestation{})\r\n\r\nFixes that panic but I have no idea if this is a meaningful solution.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
